Let's point the facts :
- The game forces login in a publisher server, which is a bad practice, even it runs offline. 
Several games did this in the past and, for some, a patch was created by the community to remove such feature;
- Have online servers implies to control all that implies in costs;
- The game does not have a "real" campaign mode. The maps can be loaded without any connection, storyline,
with, at least, by some drawings and texts. Even cheap productions does this. The game, in fact, never had a campaign mode;
- Low budget games, like NACON's Robocop, have a story and a really single player mode, which is good , by the way;
- The game is an online survival coop-game , with minimal features allowing plays solo ;
- The game is like left4dead ;
-  There are a plenty of free games that does more or less the same;
- Only buy it  in a sale, if you like the genre.

[u]This game has achieved what i seek the most in co-op Zombie games:[/u]

[b] ‚Ä¢[/b]Total adrenaline situations;
